Detailed Description

cvmx_gmx::_tx_ovr_bp

GMX_TX_OVR_BP = Packet Interface TX Override BackPressure

Notes: In XAUI mode, only the lsb (corresponding to port0) of EN, BP, and IGN_FULL are used.

GMX*_TX_OVR_BP[EN<0>] must be set to one and GMX*_TX_OVR_BP[BP<0>] must be cleared to zero (to forcibly disable HW-automatic 802.3 pause packet generation) with the HiGig2 Protocol when GMX*_HG2_CONTROL[HG2TX_EN]=0. (The HiGig2 protocol is indicated by GMX*_TX_XAUI_CTL[HG_EN]=1 and GMX*_RX0_UDD_SKP[LEN]=16.) HW can only auto-generate backpressure through HiGig2 messages (optionally, when GMX*_HG2_CONTROL[HG2TX_EN]=1) with the HiGig2 protocol.
